ZH: 我不喜欢孤单的时候哭。
EN: I don't like crying when I'm alone.

ZH: 她哭得很伤心。
EN: She cried very sadly.

ZH: 他哭得大声无比。
EN: He cried loudly.

ZH: 有时候哭可以舒缓心情。
EN: Sometimes crying can relieve stress.

ZH: 昨晚我哭着入睡。
EN: Last night I fell asleep crying.

ZH: 当我看到那些动情的电影时，我总是忍不住哭。
EN: I always can't help but cry when I watch those emotional movies.

ZH: 他哭了半个小时。
EN: He cried for half an hour.

ZH: 当我生气时，我不喜欢让别人看到我哭。
EN: When I'm angry, I don't like others to see me cry.

ZH: 别哭了，一切会好起来的。
EN: Don't cry, everything will be okay.

ZH: 我看到那一幕，哭得稀里哗啦。
EN: I saw that scene and cried my eyes out.

ZH: 他哭得眼泪汪汪。
EN: He cried with tears streaming down his face.

ZH: 她哭得伤心欲绝。
EN: She cried in despair.

ZH: 看到他这样伤心的样子我实在忍不住哭了。
EN: I couldn't help but cry when I saw him so sad.

ZH: 那个小男孩疼得哭了起来。
EN: The little boy cried in pain.

ZH: 她哭得很悲伤。
EN: She cried very sadly.

ZH: 他大声哭了起来。
EN: He burst into tears.

ZH: 她哭得几乎一整夜。
EN: She cried almost the whole night.

ZH: 哭并不能解决问题。
EN: Crying doesn't solve anything.

ZH: 他感到非常悲伤，眼泪止不住地流。
EN: He felt very sad and tears flowed uncontrollably.

ZH: 哭是一种情感的释放。
EN: Crying is a release of emotions.
